class Solution {
    public List<List<String>> groupAnagrams(String[] strs) {
        Map<String, List<String>> map = new HashMap<String, List<String>>();
        for (int i = 0; i < strs.length; i++){
            char[] cha = strs[i].toCharArray();
            Arrays.sort(cha);
            String key = String.valueOf(cha);
            if (map.containsKey(key)){
                List<String> lst = map.get(key);
                lst.add(strs[i]);
                map.put(key, lst);
            } else{
                List<String> lst = new ArrayList<String>();
                lst.add(strs[i]);
                map.put(key, lst);
            }

        }
        return new ArrayList<List<String>>(map.values());
    }
}

/
Note:

49. Group Anagrams
(1. Using HashMap when we want to group items together / store items with “String” as key.
2. Using HashSet when we just want to know if particular item exist quickly.
3. Using List to store item with “index” as key)

1.	“String.valueOf(char);“: convert char array / char to string.
	    
      char[] chararr1 = new char[] { 't', 'u', 't' };
      String str1 = String.valueOf(chararr1);

2.	“Hash_Map.values()”: Return all the values of map(without key).

      // Mapping int values to string keys
        hash_map.put("Geeks", 10);
        hash_map.put("4", 15);
        hash_map.put("Geeks", 20);
        hash_map.put("Welcomes", 25);
        hash_map.put("You", 30);
  
      // Displaying the HashMap(includes key)
        System.out.println("Initial Mappings are: " + hash_map);
  
      // Using values() to get the set view of values(without key)
        System.out.println("The collection is: " + hash_map.values());

      Output:
        Initial Mappings are: {4=15, Geeks=20, You=30, Welcomes=25}
        The collection is: [15, 20, 30, 25]

3.	“map.getOrDefault(Object key, defaultValue);”: to get the value of HashMap with specified key. 
    If no value is mapped with the provided key then the default value is returned.
    
      HashMap: {a=100, b=200, c=300, d=400}
      int k = map.getOrDefault("y", 500);
      Returned Value: 500

